500|$|<b>Trade</b> <b>union</b> <b>activist</b> and {{journalist}} Jimmy Reid wrote in The Scotsman in 2002 criticising New Labour {{for failing to}} promote or deliver equality. He argued that Labour's pursuit of a [...] "dynamic market economy" [...] {{was a way of}} continuing the operation of a free market economy, which prevented governments from interfering to achieve social justice. Reid argued that the social agenda of Clement Attlee's government was abandoned by Thatcher and not revived by New Labour. He criticised the party for not preventing inequality from widening, and argued that New Labour's ambition to win elections had moved the party towards the right.|$|E
